Lekazi Primary School received a whopping 1 500 reading books from the Management College of Southern Africa and Yusuf Karodia Foundation. This happened during the handing over of three mobile libraries at the school on February 13.   Mubeen Seedat, the director of Mancosa Gauteng, said, “Our aim of such donations is to try to encourage pupils to develop a learning culture. Read:
Learners interact with Pepper the Robot in Mbombela  We sincerely believe that developing a learning culture for every South African child will expose them to better options in life and eventually improve their welfare and status in life.” 